    <MN_SettingsEnableLoggingLabel>Enable message and warning logging</MN_SettingsEnableLoggingLabel>
    <MN_SettingsEnableLoggingDescription>When enabled, Matter Network will write message and warning logs. Errors and exceptions are always logged.</MN_SettingsEnableLoggingDescription>
    <MN_SettingsDisableNetworkItemsForWealthLabel>Disable wealth for network items</MN_SettingsDisableNetworkItemsForWealthLabel>
    <MN_SettingsDisableNetworkItemsForWealthDescription>When enabled, items stored inside Matter Network do not add to colony wealth. When disabled, network items are still counted once each instead of once per interface/controller path.</MN_SettingsDisableNetworkItemsForWealthDescription>
    <MN_SettingsEnableStoredItemPowerDrawLabel>Require power for stored items</MN_SettingsEnableStoredItemPowerDrawLabel>
    <MN_SettingsEnableStoredItemPowerDrawDescription>When enabled, networks draw extra power based on the amount of stored matter. The configured value is charged once per started 100 bytes.</MN_SettingsEnableStoredItemPowerDrawDescription>
    <MN_SettingsStoredItemPowerDrawPer100Bytes>Stored item draw per 100 bytes</MN_SettingsStoredItemPowerDrawPer100Bytes>
    <MN_SettingsNetworkPowerUsageTitle>Network building power usage</MN_SettingsNetworkPowerUsageTitle>
    <MN_SettingsNetworkPowerUsageDescription>Override the power draw each Matter Network building contributes to its connected network. Values are in watts and are applied to all matching defs.</MN_SettingsNetworkPowerUsageDescription>
